{"ts": "2026-06-08T05:05:11.210373+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 8a4ac4574ce42d8110ae85af25204557c5dc8f9a)", "id": "lc_7f1b50ea-bb3f-464d-b148-377fe79ac90e"}, {"type": "text", "text": "[tool.poetry]\nname = \"fastapi-template\"\nversion = \"1.3.0\"\n\nauthors = [\"Donny Peeters <donny.peeters@hotmail.com>\"]\nmaintainers = [\"Donny Peeters <donny.peeters@hotmail.com>\"]\ndescription = \"A FastAPI and SQLAlchemy project template with Docker and GitHub Actions.\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nhomepage = \"https://github.com/Donnype/fastapi-template\"\nrepository = \"https://github.com/Donnype/fastapi-template\"\nkeywords = [\"FastAPI\", \"Template\"]\n\n\n[tool.poetry.dependencies]\npython = \"^3.10\"\nrequests = \"^2.32.4\"\nfastapi = \"^0.115.2\"\nuvicorn = \"^0.32.0\"\nSQLAlchemy = \"^1.4.42\"\nalembic = \"^1.8.1\"\npsycopg2-binary = \"^2.9.9\"\n\n[tool.poetry.group.dev]\noptional = true\n\n[tool.poetry.group.dev.dependencies]\nhttpx = \"^0.27.0\"\npytest = \"^7.4.4\"\npre-commit = \"^3.5.0\"\n\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"poetry-core\"]\nbuild-backend = \"poetry.core.masonry.api\"\n\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\nmarkers = [\n    \"unit: mark a test as a unit test.\",\n    \"integration: mark test as an integration test.\",\n]\n\n[tool.black]\ntarget-version = [\"py310\"]\nline-length = 120\n\n[tool.vulture]\nmin_confidence = 90\nexclude = [\"/tests/\", \"*venv*\"]\npaths = [\".\"]\n\n[tool.ruff]\nselect = [\"E\", \"F\", \"ERA\", \"W\", \"TID\", \"I\", \"G\", \"INP\", \"T20\", \"UP\", \"ISC\", \"PTH\", \"SIM\", \"PLC\", \"A\"]\nignore = [\"UP006\", \"UP007\", \"A003\", \"T201\", \"T203\"]\nfix = true\nline-length = 120\ntarget-version = \"py310\"\ntask-tags = [\"Example\", \"todo\", \"TODO\", \"FIXME\"]\n", "id": "lc_61d34036-47b4-4678-ab5a-b5d058d4d289"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "aa89c173-f2a1-4c85-a54a-89bb5ced6bd3", "tool_call_id": "call_01_o1HvbwnYKmBikl865gzO1377", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T05:05:11.312597+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 6d39a0b3ffedb4da136abb7c078b7b47e11c272a)", "id": "lc_7473d71a-4189-4e32-95d0-6d1ef1bc72b8"}, {"type": "text", "text": "version: \"3.7\"\n\nservices:\n  unit:\n    build:\n      context: ..\n      dockerfile: api/Dockerfile\n      target: test\n    environment:\n      - DB_STRING=postgresql://postgres:test@ci_db:5432/postgres\n\n  integration:\n    depends_on:\n      - ci_db\n    build:\n      context: ..\n      dockerfile: api/Dockerfile\n      target: test\n    environment:\n      - DB_STRING=postgresql://postgres:test@ci_db:5432/postgres\n\n  ci_db:\n    image: postgres:14.5\n    environment:\n      - POSTGRES_PASSWORD=test\n", "id": "lc_7df7afe9-9764-4f89-9ae2-0560b49efdc8"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "1c2a28fd-4d5a-40ae-833e-9ebe015c8f2d", "tool_call_id": "call_00_mJDh98XRk3gNSMvXJ8jw3835", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T05:05:36.332125+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have a complete picture of the testing organization. Here's the explanation:\n\n---\n\n## Testing Organization in This FastAPI Template\n\n### Where Tests Live\nAll tests reside in a single file: **`api/test_all.py`**. There is no separate `tests/` directory — the test file sits alongside the application code.\n\n### How Unit and Integration Tests Are Separated\n\nSeparation is achieved through **pytest markers**, not by directory structure.\n\n| Marker | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `@pytest.mark.unit` | Marks a test as a **unit test** — fast, no external dependencies |\n| `@pytest.mark.integration` | Marks a test as an **integration test** — requires a real database |\n\nThese markers are registered in **`pyproject.toml`** under `[tool.pytest.ini_options]`:\n\n```toml\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\nmarkers = [\n    \"unit: mark a test as a unit test.\",\n    \"integration: mark test as an integration test.\",\n]\n```\n\n### Fixtures & Test Doubles\n\n- **Unit tests** use the `fake_todo_repository` fixture, which provides an **`InMemoryTodoRepository`** — a pure in-memory fake with no database dependency.\n- **Integration tests** use the `todo_repository` fixture, which runs Alembic migrations, creates a real **`SQLTodoRepository`** backed by PostgreSQL, and tears down tables afterward.\n- There is also a **contract test** (`test_contract_test`) that runs the *same assertions* against both repositories, ensuring the fake and the real implementation behave identically (a pattern Martin Fowler calls [Contract Test](https://martinfowler.com/bliki/ContractTest.html)).\n\n### Testing the HTTP Layer\n\nAPI-level integration tests use Starlette’s **`TestClient`** (imported from `starlette.testclient`) to call the FastAPI app directly without starting a real server:\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.integration\ndef test_api():\n    client = TestClient(app)\n    response = client.post(\"/create/testkey?value=testvalue\")\n    assert response.status_code == 201\n    ...\n```\n\n### Make Targets That Run Tests\n\nAll test orchestration is defined in the **Makefile** at the repo root:\n\n| Target | Command | What it does |\n|--------|---------|--------------|\n| `make test` | `utest` + `itest` | Runs **both** unit and integration tests |\n| `make utest` | `pytest -m unit .` | Runs **unit tests only** (inside the `unit` Docker service) |\n| `make itest` | `pytest -m integration .` | Runs **integration tests only** (inside the `integration` Docker service, which depends on a PostgreSQL container) |\n| `make check` | `pre-commit run -a` | Runs linting/formatting checks (also in the `unit` container) |\n| `make done` | `check` + `test` | Full pre-commit validation: lint + all tests |\n| `make cleantest` | `docker compose kill/down/build` | Tears down and rebuilds test containers to ensure a clean state |\n\n### CI / Docker Infrastructure\n\nThe `.ci/docker-compose.yml` defines three services:\n\n- **`unit`** — builds the `test` stage of `api/Dockerfile`; runs unit tests (no database dependency).\n- **`integration`** — same image but **depends on `ci_db`**; receives `DB_STRING=postgresql://postgres:test@ci_db:5432/postgres` so SQLAlchemy/Alembic can connect.\n- **`ci_db`** — stock `postgres:14.5` image with password `test`.\n\nThe Makefile references this compose file via the `ci-compose` variable:\n```makefile\nci-compose := docker compose -f .ci/docker-compose.yml\n```\n\n### Summary\n\n- **No separate test directories** — one file, two marker-based taxonomies.\n- **`make utest`** → unit tests (`-m unit`), in-memory fakes, no DB.\n- **`make itest`** → integration tests (`-m integration`), real PostgreSQL via Docker, plus HTTP-level tests with `TestClient`.\n- **`make test`** → both.\n- Docker Compose in `.ci/` provides isolated, reproducible test environments.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"to